The human brain — it’s about the size of two fists put together, weighs roughly 1.4 kilograms, and yet it runs everything you do. #line:0d45de9 

It controls your movements, stores your memories, processes your thoughts, and even keeps your heart beating without you thinking about it. #line:07dcae6 

Without your brain, you couldn’t speak, dream, or even recognize your best friend’s face. #line:0d7ddef 

It’s like the ultimate control center, made of billions of nerve cells that talk to each other in tiny electrical sparks. #line:0467ba8 

Today, we’re going to explore the brain’s five major lobes — each with its own special powers. #line:0d0705c 
