The "parietal lobe" is like your brain's touch and taste center. It is like your your brain's GPS, helping you understand where your body is in space and how to move it. #line:0bdb34d 
It processes touch sensations, like feeling a soft blanket or the warmth of the sun on your skin.  #line:0d07134 
It also helps you understand where your body is in space, so you can touch your nose with your eyes closed or catch a ball without looking.  #line:0e71c25 

