Next, let's zoom in on the very front tip of the frontal lobe.  #line:0f06808 

Think of it as the CEO's desk inside the brian's head office. This is where the big, complex thinking happens. #line:06b7d25 
It helps you plan for the future, make decisions and weighs pros and cons. It also acts like a brake pedal, helping you control impuses so you dont just do the first thing that pops into your head.  #line:0a08cf8 
When you're remembering something just long enough to use it-like a phone number before you dial-it's the prefrontal cortex that helps you keep that information in mind. #line:075aecc 
It even shapes your social behavior and personality, guiding how you interact with people and read social cues. #line:0904ae5 

Fun fact, this part of the brian isnt fully development until your mid twenties, which is why teenagers sometimes make impulsive decisions. #line:0432e92 
