The cerebellum is like the brain's balance and coordination center. It helps you keep your balance when you walk, ride a bike, or dance. #line:03807f8 
It’s also responsible for fine motor skills, like writing or playing an instrument. When you learn a new skill, like riding a bike, the cerebellum helps you practice until it becomes second nature. #line:0be89c7 
Without it, walking or even holding a cup steady would be tough! #line:0773ac5 

