Now, look at the brainstem — that stalk-like structure right at the center bottom, under the brain. #line:0012915 

It’s the vital connection between your brain and spinal cord, managing life-essential functions like breathing and heartbeat. It’s a true life-support hub. #line:0e13ba8 
The brainstem is like the brain's autopilot. It controls all the automatic functions that keep you alive, like breathing, heart rate, and blood pressure. #line:088011e 
It’s also responsible for basic reflexes, like blinking when something comes close to your eyes or pulling your hand away from something hot. #line:0769a00 

