Here’s the thalamus and the surrounding midbrain structures, the central bulge just above the brainstem. #line:001bed5 

Think of it as the brain’s relay station — it channels sensory information to the cerebral cortex so you can make sense of the world. It’s like a traffic cop, directing signals from your senses to the right parts of the brain. #line:06c7b76 

